[[Image:Nain rug.jpg|thumb|right|250px|A round Nain rug.]]

'''Nain rugs''' are constructed using the [[Persian knot]] and typically have between 300 and 700 [[knot density|knots per]] [[square inch]].{{cn|date=June 2016}} The [[Knotted-pile_carpet|pile]] is usually very high quality [[wool]], clipped short, and [[silk]] is often used as highlighting for detail in the design.{{cn|date=June 2016}}

