'''Orlaith Rafter''' is an [[Irish people|Irish]] actor, novelist and playwright. She is known to television viewers as the character [[Robin McKenna]] in long-running soap opera ''[[Fair City]]''.
She was interviewed for the special ''A Fair City for Love''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rte.ie/tv/christmas/faircity.html|title=A Fair City for Love|work=RTÉ}}</ref> She is on record as saying she is nothing like her screen character in ''Fair City''. Cars do not interest her and neither do material things.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://tribune.maithu.com/archive/article/2003/nov/02/dream-machine-orlaith-rafter-flashy-cars-dont-impr/|title=Orlaith Rafter: Flashy cars don't impress me much|date=2 November 2003|accessdate=2 November 2003|first=Paddy|last=Comyn|work=[[Sunday Tribune]]}}</ref>
Rafter is currently on a year of absence from ''Fair City''. She wrote her first play, ''Mercury Memory'', during this time.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.herald.ie/entertainment/around-town/curtain-up-as-fair-citys-orlaith-pens-her-first-play-2209287.html|title=Curtain up as Fair City's Orlaith pens her first play|date=5 June 2010|accessdate=5 June 2010|first=Lorna|last=Nolan|work=Evening Herald|publisher=Independent News & Media}}</ref> She is also experimenting with novel writing but intends to eventually return to the screen.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.herald.ie/entertainment/around-town/write-stuff-orlaith-takes-break-from-fair-city-to-pen-her-first-novel-1730065.html|title=Write stuff: Orlaith takes break from Fair City to pen her first novel|date=6 May 2009|accessdate=6 May 2009|first=Lorna|last=Nolan|work=Evening Herald|publisher=Independent News & Media}}</ref>
She married IT worker Mick Quinlan in 2011.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.ie/incoming/incoming_dailyfeed/bride-and-joy-for-fair-citys-orlaith-2969498.html|title=Bride and joy for Fair City's Orlaith|date=21 December 2011|accessdate=21 December 2011|work=Irish Independent|publisher=Independent News & Media}}</ref>
